criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  -  Self-identified as African American or Black;

  -  Aged 18 years or older;

  -  High school graduate or GED;

  -  Smoking at least 10 cigarettes daily for the past year;

  -  Usually smoked mentholated cigarette brand (greater than 80% of the time) in the past
     two years;

  -  Good physical health (no unstable medical condition);

  -  No contraindications for nicotine inhaler or gum use, such as mouth sores or
     significant dental or jaw problems;

  -  Stable, good health.

Exclusion Criteria:

  -  Recent unstable or untreated psychiatric diagnosis including substance abuse, as
     determined by the DSM-IV criteria;

  -  Currently using other tobacco or nicotine products other than cigarettes;

  -  Pregnant or nursing.
